{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": \"Looking at /root/.claude.json, tell me which mcp servers are currently configured.\", \"role\": \"user\"}, {\"content\": [{\"text\": \"I'll read the Claude configuration file to see which MCP servers are configured.\", \"type\": \"text\"}, {\"id\": \"toolu_01BKy9qgJg7s4zFGViAvTZRq\", \"input\": {\"file_path\": \"/root/.claude.json\"}, \"name\": \"Read\", \"type\": \"tool_use\"}], \"role\": \"assistant\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_01Uz26yd6C8F34vGHP56v7gR", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Based on the `/root/.claude.json` configuration file, there are **2 MCP servers** currently configured for the `/code` project:\n\n## Configured MCP Servers:\n\n1. **`imbue`**\n   - Command: `imbue-cli.sh`\n   - Args: `--log-to-file=/tmp/imbue-cli.log mcp --project-path /code --use-internal-config --transport stdio`\n   - Transport: stdio\n\n2. **`imbue_tools`**\n   - Command: `imbue-cli.sh`\n   - Args: `--log-to-file=/tmp/imbue-cli.log mcp --project-path /code --config /code/tools.toml --transport stdio`\n   - Transport: stdio\n\nAdditionally, there's a global MCP server defined (not project-specific):\n\n3. **`dummy`** (global scope)\n   - Type: HTTP\n   - URL: `https://example.com`\n\nThe two main servers (`imbue` and `imbue_tools`) are both using the Imbue CLI and are configured specifically for this project at `/code`. They differ in that one uses internal config while the other uses a custom config file at `/code/tools.toml`."}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 6, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 15308, "cache_read_input_tokens": 12181, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 15308, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 298, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
